PO.Data: The theme to use as the default on startup. Should match the folder name under zkwebui/theme. Also see the ZK Theme Maintenance window.
Text used as a title in "about" windows.
Integer priority - used as a fall back to determine theme of choice
The theme name should match the folder name under zkwebui/theme. For example adempiere_default.
The list of possible theme origin types.
Theme origins can be FOLDER or JAR. For more info see http://www.zkoss.org/javadoc/7.0.1/zk/org/zkoss/web/theme/StandardTheme.ThemeOrigin.html.
The theme is contained in a folder structure
The theme is stored in a jar archive.
The type of theme structure. Can be a FOLDER or JAR based theme.
An interger indicating the relative priority of this theme.
The priority is compared to other themes to select the theme to use if cookies and library functions do not provide a theme.
Is this theme to be the default theme used on startup?
The first highest priority theme selected as default will be used by the system at startup.
Is the theme to be cached?
If the theme is to be cached, the cache hours determine how long to keep the cache. Deselecting this field will turn caching off.
The number of hours that the theme won't be changed and client can safely cache the file.

The client is allowed to cache the theme file until the returned hours expires. If it is never changed until next ZK upgrade, you could return 8760 (the default). If you don't want the client to cache, return a non-positive number.
The URI or path to the theme resource from the theme directory. This is primarily for injecting custom css files to the theme.
The wildcard pattern "~./" can be used to represent the theme. The theme provider will resolve the full path. Alternatively, specify the path from the root (zkwebui) directory.
Themes available to the ZK interface.
This table maintains the list of themes or styles that can be applied to the ZK interface.
A Client is a company or a legal entity. You cannot share data between Clients. Tenant is a synonym for Client.
An organization is a unit of your client or legal entity - examples are store, department. You can share data between organizations.
The record is active in the system

There are two methods of making records unavailable in the system: One is to delete the record, the other is to de-activate the record. A de-activated record is not available for selection, but available for reports. There are two reasons for de-activating and not deleting records: (1) The system requires the record for audit purposes. (2) The record is referenced by other records. E.g., you cannot delete a Business Partner, if there are invoices for this partner record existing. You de-activate the Business Partner and prevent that this record is used for future entries.
The Created field indicates the date that this record was created.
The Updated field indicates the date that this record was updated.
The Created By field indicates the user who created this record.
The Updated By field indicates the user who updated this record.
Optional short description of the record
A description is limited to 255 characters.
The Help field contains a hint, comment or help about the use of this item.
Search key for the record in the format required - must be unique

A search key allows you a fast method of finding a particular record. If you leave the search key empty, the system automatically creates a numeric number. The document sequence used for this fallback number is defined in the "Maintain Sequence" window with the name "DocumentNo_<TableName>", where TableName is the actual name of the table (e.g. C_Order).
